    <note>Li(2) Xuan(2) [1033] His ancestors were Tang imperial clansmen (zongshi), who fled the rebellions and settled in Qiongzhou, Yizheng xian. Probably this family is another branch of the lineage of Chang(2) Gou's [7118] wife, which was established by the Tang Yantie panguan, Li(2) Gai [3511], who followed Xizong into Sichuan and settled in Qiongzhou, Yizheng xian. None of his patrilineal kin of the three previous generations held office. His grandfather used his talents to become well-known (zhu) in the community. Xuan was orphaned at three and his elder brother, Tao [3531], educated him. Ji(2)'s [989] father. XCB, 148.8b, 153.3b, 172.8a; SS, 302.20a; Sichuan TZ, 122.13a (jinshi #3, mingzi with jade radical in error); Sima Guang, WJ, 78.7a-9a. CBD, 2, 886.</note>
